41:19.550 --> 41:27.190
vehicle is fully reusable, and it's the first spaceship that we've ever built
for that purpose. In fact, its the first spaceship that's ever been built

41:27.190 --> 41:41.210
anywhere for that purpose. Some interesting figures, the mercury program,
Gemini, Apollo, all used a blade-y material because it was a one-time use. And

41:41.210 --> 41:50.210
it heated and sloughed off and that was it. When we started talking about the
shuttle, we had to do something that could be reusable without this giant

41:50.210 --> 42:04.490
turnaround problem of trying to replace bladers. The decision was made to use a
rigidized silica fiber, it's glass. You hold one of these tiles, which is

42:04.490 --> 42:14.550
typically six inches or so square, anywhere from two to three inches in
thickness, and it feels like a piece of styrofoam. It's very, very light. And if

42:14.550 --> 42:24.650
you look at the next chart, which is not a very good picture, I wanted to try to
