42:24.650 --> 42:40.970
fiber that's shown here, this is a microscopic view and the rigidized fiber is a
99.6% pure silica. And it's in a it's in a cut fiber length that's mixed with

42:40.970 --> 42:52.490
liquid silica which we call Ludox to make a slurry. It is then pressed into the
right volume to get the density we want, which is about 9 pounds per cubic foot.

42:53.230 --> 43:04.250
And it's then baked at 2,400 degrees for some length of time. And it forms a
very hard brick of this very light material. It's then machined with a milling

43:04.250 --> 43:13.170
machine computerized to very tight tolerances because it must match a smooth
service on the outside of the vehicle.

43:15.910 --> 43:24.970
The coating that we put over that, because this is very soft. you can poke your
